main event: Four oval-shaped objects were observed by weather station employees moving at high speeds, stopping and hovering, then continuing at a high rate of speed.
interesting points: The objects were silver in color and appeared to have no wings or tail surfaces.
The objects were observed through binoculars and a telescope and were larger than commercial aircraft.
The light reflecting off the objects was intense, but no sound was heard.
The Air Force investigators concluded that the objects were likely aircraft or weather balloons, and no further investigation was warranted.
witnesses: employees at an area weather station
